# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your own free-tier keys.
# Never commit the real .env.local file.
#
# Every key below is OPTIONAL except the Firebase ones. Leave any of the
# others blank and that feature automatically falls back to cached/mock
# data — the app never crashes or breaks from a missing key.
#
# IMPORTANT — read this once: every VITE_-prefixed variable is bundled
# into the client-side JavaScript and is visible to anyone who opens
# DevTools on your deployed site. That's an inherent trade-off of running
# 100% client-side with no backend (which is the whole point of this
# refactor — no Cloud Functions, no Blaze plan required). Mitigate it by
# restricting each key's allowed referrers/domains in its respective
# provider dashboard once you deploy. Do not reuse these keys for
# anything sensitive.

# Firebase (Spark/free tier project) — from Firebase Console > Project Settings
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=

# OpenWeatherMap free tier — get one instantly at openweathermap.org/api
# Without this, the weather screen shows clearly-labeled mock data.
VITE_OPENWEATHER_API_KEY=

# data.gov.in / Agmarknet — get a free key at data.gov.in (My Account >
# API Keys) after signing up. NOT in your original requested list, but
# added because Agmarknet requires its own distinct key from data.gov.in,
# separate from OpenWeatherMap or Gemini — there's no way to call it
# without one. Without this key, or if data.gov.in's CORS policy blocks
# the browser request (genuinely uncertain — see comments in
# src/lib/mandi.ts), mandi prices fall back to cached or mock data, both
# clearly labeled as such in the UI rather than presented as live.
VITE_AGMARKNET_API_KEY=

# Google AI Studio free Gemini API — get one instantly, no card required,
# at aistudio.google.com/apikey. Only used if VITE_LLM_EXTRACTION_ENABLED
# is also "true" below; without it, the fabrication module's free,
# always-on rule-based extractor handles requests with no loss of core
# functionality.
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=
VITE_LLM_EXTRACTION_ENABLED=false
